The paper focuses on image processing and restoration using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of burst photography and optimization methods also suggests a potential fit for machine learning (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of proximal gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
